It gets philosophized as "Chinese pragmatism" in the West, but is closer to Italian mercenaries' and spies' constant opportunism. Chinese betray their masters constantly as if frolicking and playing, always in their own interest.

"China is not chess, but billiards." - Galkvosky.

Dmitry Galkovsky had an interesting argument about how Chinese people's racial nature is "Southern" and "Italian", e.g. Chinese spies and communists were completely non-ideological and would work for anyone who was willing to pay them money and later betray them without any care.

And of course this is not done for selfish reasons or laziness, but to secure the wellbeing of one's own family and relatives. Chinese people love their families (and thus homeland) and always want to leave a good inheritance to their descendants and have this idea of continuity.
